00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:04.840
 We have discovered manuscripts that go back to the 2nd century.

00:00:04.840 --> 00:00:12.479
 And what's on the screen for you is a copy of a late 2nd century, early 3rd century copy of the Gospel of John.

00:00:12.479 --> 00:00:14.279
 It's called P66.

00:00:14.279 --> 00:00:18.719
 And that's because scholars are very imaginative, and it's made out of papyrus, so they said,

