00:00:25.000 --> 00:00:28.959
 It takes doctoral-level work to figure that kind of stuff out.

00:00:28.959 --> 00:00:34.559
 But what's really interesting about P66 is that if we're dealing with a book with a codex,

00:00:34.559 --> 00:00:43.600
